getAllConfigNamesTimeStamp().notice: Gets all names of timestamp configuration entries.

getAllNames().notice: Gets all names in the directory.

getCheckpointBlockNumber(bytes32,uint256.notice: Gets the full checkpoint (value and activation key) for a block number configuration entry at a specific index.

getCheckpointTimeStamp(bytes32,uint256).notice: Gets the full checkpoint (value and activation key) for a timestamp configuration entry at a specific index.

getConfigBlockNumber(bytes32,uint256).notice: Gets the block number configuration value at a specific index for a configuration entry.

getConfigNameBlockNumber(bytes32).notice: Gets the name of a block number configuration entry by its name digest.

getConfigNameTimeStamp(bytes32).notice: Gets the name of a timestamp configuration entry by its name digest.

getConfigTimeStamp(bytes32,uint256).notice: Gets the timestamp configuration value at a specific index for a configuration entry.

getName(bytes32).notice: Gets the name by keccak256 hash of the name.

getNumCheckpointsBlockNumber(bytes32).notice: Gets the number of checkpoints for a block number configuration entry.

getNumCheckpointsTimeStamp(bytes32).notice: Gets the number of checkpoints for a timestamp configuration entry.

removeAddress(string).notice: Removes an address from the directory by name.

replaceAddress(string,address).notice: Replaces an existing address in the directory by name.

semver().notice: Returns the semantic version of the contract implementation. Refer to https://semver.org/
